  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Potentially longer sentences for aggravated cases\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial fines, often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the funds involved\n- Asset forfeiture and seizure of funds connected to laundering activities\n\n3. Additional consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Potential professional license revocation\n- Loss of certain civil rights\n- Deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like the amount of money involved, prior criminal history, and specific circumstances of the offense. Federal prosecutors typically pursue these cases under statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.",
